== Œuvres ==

* ''General Sherman's Official Account of His Great March to Georgia and the Carolinas, from His Departure from Chattanooga to the Surrender of General Joseph E. Johnston and Confederate Forces under His Command'' (1865)
* ''Autobiography, 1828-1861'' (circa 1868), Mss. 57, WTS Papers, Ohio Historical Society. Souvenirs privés pour les enfants de Sherman.
* ''Memoirs of General William T. Sherman, Written by Himself'' (1875).
* ''Reports of Inspection Made in the Summer of 1877 by Generals P. H. Sheridan and W. T. Sherman of Country North of the Union Pacific Railroad'' (co-auteur, 1878)
* [http://books.google.com/books?id=bUUYJ9oYN7wC&printsec=frontcover&dq=sherman+letters#PPR1,M1 ''The Sherman Letters: Correspondence between General and Senator Sherman from 1837 to 1891'' (posthume, 1894)]
* [http://books.google.com/books?id=-iz2dbO65skC&printsec=frontcover&dq=home+letters#PPP15,M1 ''Home Letters of General Sherman'' (posthume, 1909)]
* [http://books.google.com/books?id=fC4WAAAAIAAJ&printsec=frontcover&dq=Fleming+SHerman&lr=#PPA5,M1 ''General W. T. Sherman as College President: A Collection of Letters, Documents, and Other Material, Chiefly from Private Sources, Relating to the Life and Activities of General William Tecumseh Sherman, to the Early Years of Louisiana State University, and the Stirring Conditions Existing in the South on the Eve of the Civil War'' (posthume, 1912)]
* ''The William Tecumseh Sherman Family Letters'' (posthume, 1967). Collection de microfilms préparés par les Archives de l'Université de Notre-Dame contenant des lettres, etc., de Sherman, son épouse, et d'autres.
* ''Sherman at War'' (posthume, 1992)
* ''Sherman's Civil War: Selected Correspondence of William T. Sherman, 1860 – 1865'' (posthume, 1999)

